aesdpy.work¶

aesdpy.work.cancel(api_url, model_id, work_id)¶

Cancel work.

Parameters:
  • api_url (string) – A url to query
  • model_id (string) – A model ID
  • work_id (string) – A work ID
Returns:

result
Return type:

json

Examples

aesdpy.work.remove success¶
import aesdpy
aesdpy.work.cancel('http://1lv11lamb01.nrel.gov:8090', 'f0', 'abc')

# Returns:
# {
#     'result': 'ok'
# }
aesdpy.work.cancel failure¶
import aesdpy
aesdpy.work.cancel('http://1lv11lamb01.nrel.gov:8090', 'f0', 'abc')

# Returns:
#
# {
#     'error': {
#         'status': 400,
#         'message': 'Bad Request',
#         'description': 'not supported'
#     }
# }

API Info:

DELETE /models/{model_id}/work/{work}¶
Response JSON Object:
 
  • result (string) – the result of delete

aesdpy.work.get(api_url, model_id, work_id)¶

Get a specific work.

Parameters:
  • api_url (string) – A url to query
  • model_id (string) – A model ID
  • work_id (string) – A work ID
Returns:

A work
Return type:

json

Example

aesdpy.work.get success¶
import aesdpy
aesdpy.work.get('http://1lv11lamb01.nrel.gov:8090', 'f0', 'X7Rsg')

# Returns:
# {
#     "status": "success",
#     "work_id": "X7Rsg",
#     "result_id": "NIKm9EnR3hjvfV"
# }
aesdpy.work.get failure 1¶
import aesdpy
aesdpy.work.get('http://1lv11lamb01.nrel.gov:8090', 'f0', 'abcd')

# Response:
# {
#     'error': {
#         'status': 400,
#         'message': 'Bad Request',
#         'description': 'work not found'
#     }
# }

API Info:

GET /models/{model_id}/work/{work_id}¶
Response JSON Object:
 
  • status (string) – work status
  • work_id (string) – a work ID
  • additional – a additional ID
Status Codes:
  • 200 OK – json
  • 400 Bad Request – error description
  • 500 Internal Server Error – error description
aesdpy.work.issue(api_url, model_id, body={})¶

Issue work.

Parameters:
  • api_url (string) – A url to query
  • model_id (string) – A model ID
  • body (json) – Work to issue
Returns:

work submission result
Return type:

json

Examples

aesdpy.work.issue success¶
import aesdpy
work = {
    'explicit': [
        {
            'id': 'Pw0Z'
            'value': 2.0
        }
    ],
    'random': [
        'nZ'
    ],
    'timeout': 60,
    'priority': 0
}
aesdpy.work.issue('http://1lv11lamb01.nrel.gov:8090', 'XXp', work)

# Returns:
# {
#     "work_id": "abc",
#     "generation": 42,
#     "estimated_completion": 123
# }

API Info:

POST /models/{model_id}/work¶
Request JSON Object:
 
  • explicit (array(dict)) –
  • random (array(string)) –
  • timeout (int) –
  • priority (int) –
Status Codes:
  • 200 OK – json
  • 400 Bad Request – error description
  • 500 Internal Server Error – error description
aesdpy.work.list(api_url, model_id, query={})¶

Get all work. Provide tag information in query to search for specific items.

Parameters:
  • api_url (string) – A url to query
  • model_id (string) – A model ID
  • query (json) – The query params
Returns:

A set of work
Return type:

json

Examples

aesdpy.work.list success 1¶
import aesdpy
aesdpy.work.list('http://1lv11lamb01.nrel.gov:8090', 'XXp')

# Returns:
# [
#     {
#         "status": "success",
#         "work_id": "OGXnJpuRgSvU7KpTXpXY06",
#         "result_id": "Il81Na1b665QiXyF"
#     },
#     ...
# ]
aesdpy.work.list success 2¶
import aesdpy
aesdpy.work.list('http://1lv11lamb01.nrel.gov:8090', 'f0', {'status': 'failed'})

# Returns:
# [
#     {
#         "status": "failed",
#         "work_id": "pRXld2YbWfN1c8XU4d0tVp5Q",
#         "additional": "0uLKujNXJwh6qV8LAqQTrCjQs0Dd"
#     },
#     ...
# ]

API Info:

GET /models/{model_id}/work¶
Parameters:
  • status (string) – a tag ID
  • from (string) – start generation
  • to (string) – end generation
Response JSON Object:
 
  • status (string) – work status
  • work_id (string) – a work ID
  • additional – a additional ID
Status Codes:
  • 200 OK – json
  • 400 Bad Request – error description
  • 500 Internal Server Error – error description
